earth_description.remarks: Layer almost entirely roof tiles and brick. Large quantities of copper slag. Portions of the soil becomes yellow-orange, possibly from brick decay, but the color is too inconsistent to be a new stratum. We removed this layer in steps of 20cm. The soil consisted of cobble-sized mudbrick & iron slag.  Reopened in the 2022 season.

supervisor: Jon Cashion, Dagmar Niemeijer, Stelle Gray
